summary: People are so shocked that Scott and Rhodey mentioned “Hot Tub Time Machine” in Endgame. But I am like what about Tony...
body:
People are so shocked that Scott and Rhodey mentioned “Hot Tub Time Machine” in Endgame. But I am like what about Tony referencing “Big Lebowski.” Because you know who IS that character?

Who cares if Sebastian Stan was in that first movie?? It could be the same with another actor playing the part, but you can’t have Lebowski without Bridges.

summary: The saddest part about that ending
body:
The saddest part about that ending

I think I figured out why Tony Stark dying feels so wrong to me, despite it making sense thematically for the character. We know how hard Robert Downey Jr. fought to get Tony Stark his family. Whether it was fighting to including Gwyneth Paltrow in Avengers 1, or getting Tony and Pepper back together and engaged all in a two minute scene in Spider-Man Homecoming. Now it feels like Marvel killed Tony BECAUSE he had a family. Like if Tony didn’t have the most to lose in this fight, things might have turned out very differently. So it feels like all of Robert’s hard work he put in to create this character is what caused his death. And that is so unfair to me. Maybe I’m wrong, but I think that’s why I’m still so upset about everything, and why I really need to hear how Robert Downey Jr. feels about the ending.

by faerialchemist

*CONTAINS AVENGERS ENDGAME SPOILERS*

Time was of the essence. Janet van Dyne knew there was a chance she would not be able to restore Stark’s hand that wore the gauntlet, but she could keep his soul in his body. What good was the ability to heal if she didn’t use it?

Hope landed her behind a small crowd who had gathered in front of the legendary Tony Stark. As tempted as Janet was to push her way to the front and heal him immediately, she waited. And she watched.

Time was ticking.

(An Endgame Fix-It.)
